{{Infobox person | name = <!-- include middle initial, if not specified in birth_name --> | image = <!-- filename only, no "File:" or "Image:" prefix, and no enclosing [[brackets]] --> | alt = <!-- descriptive text for use by speech synthesis (text-to-speech) software --> | caption = | birth_name = Paola Florencia Carosella | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1972|10|30}} | birth_place = [[Buenos Aires, Argentina]] | death_date = | death_place = | nationality = Argentine and Italian | other_names = | occupation = [[Chef]] | years_active = 1990-present | known_for = | notable_works = | children = 1 | website = {{URL|http://www.paolacarosella.com.br/}} }}
'''Paola Florencia Carosella''' (born October 10, 1972) is an [[Italian Argentine]] cook, businesswoman, executive and chef.
== Biography == Paola was born in [[Argentina]], the only daughter of a middle-class family. Her grandparents, both the paternal and the maternal, are from [[Italy]]. Her father, the Italian Roberto Carosella, was a photographer and racing driver, while her mother, Irma Polverari, built a successful career as a lawyer.<ref>{{citar web |url=http://vejasp.abril.com.br/cidades/paola-carosella-perfil-masterchef/ |título=Paola Carosella brilha na nova temporada de ‘MasterChef’ |acessodata=16 de agosto de 2017 |acessomesdia= |acessoano= |nocaps= |autor= |ultimo= |primeiro= |autorlink= |coautores= |data= |ano= |mes= |formato= |obra= |publicado=Veja São Paulo |páginas= |língua= Portuguese}}</ref>
She was introduced to the kitchen by her grandmothers, who planted and harvested the foods to be prepared, after finishing the correspondent to high school in the country, she began to work in restaurants in Buenos Aires. Paola currently works at [[MasterChef (Brazilian TV series)|MasterChef Brazil]] as a juror alongside Brazilian Henrique Fogaça and French chef Érick Jacquin.
On November 7, 2016, Paola released her first book which is a mix of autobiography and a collection of recipes, called "Todas as sextas".
== Gastronomic career == She worked with Argentine chef [[Francis Mallmann]] before traveling to [[Paris]] and working in restaurants such as [[Le Grand Véfour]], Le Celadon and Le Bristol.<ref name="bio" /> She even worked as a cook in restaurants in [[California]], the [[United States]], and [[Uruguay]], before moving to [[Mendoza, Argentina]], in 1994, and working at the Patagonia West restaurant in [[New York City]].
=== A Figueira Rubaiyat === In 2001, she was invited to move to [[São Paulo, Brazil]], to open and direct the kitchen of the restaurant A Figueira Rubaiyat, along with [[Francis Mallmann]] and Belarmino Fernandez Iglesias.<ref>{{Citar web |acessodata=13 de maio de 2015 |url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/saopaulo/2014/12/1556494-paola-carosella-quer-ter-programa-de-tv-para-ensinar-a-cozinhar.shtml |primeiro=Fernando |último=Silva |data=7 de dezembro de 2014 |publicado=[[Folha de S. Paulo]] |título=Paola Carosella quer ter programa de TV para ensinar a cozinhar - 07/12/2014 - são paulo - Folha de S.Paulo}}</ref>
