{{Infobox scientist |name = Rolv Petter Amdam |image = |image_size = 100px |caption = |birth_date = 7 February 1953 |birth_place = [[Ørskog]], Norway |death_date = |death_place = |residence = |citizenship = |nationality = [[Norway|Norwegian]] |ethnicity = |field = [[Business History]], [[Business Education]] |work_institutions = [[BI Norwegian Business School]] |alma_mater = [[University of Oslo]] |doctoral_advisor = |doctoral_students = |known_for = [[International Business]] |influences = |influenced = |prizes = |religion = |footnotes = }} '''Rolv Petter Storvik Amdam''' (born 7 February 1953) is a Norwegian [[economic history|economic historian]].<ref name=facpage>[http://www.bi.no/BI-Startpage2/Research/Academic-homepage/?ansattid=/fag88010 Rolv Petter Amdam]'s page at the BI Norwegian Business School website. Accessed on 2010-01-17.</ref><ref name=oxford>Oxford Handbook of Business History , ed. G. Jones & J Zertlin, 2008</ref>
He was born in [[Ørskog]].<ref name=50ar>{{cite news|title=Rolv Petter Storvik Amdam 50 år 7. februar |agency=[[Norwegian News Agency]]|language=Norwegian}}</ref> During his young days he was a member of the [[Workers' Communist Party (Norway)|Workers' Communist Party]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://ret-web01.int.retriever.no/services/webdocument.html?documentId=00230520091030123557361&serviceId=2|title=- Hvis du er i en sekt stiller du ikke spørsmål|last=Meland|first=Astrid|date=30 October 2009|work=Dagbladet|language=Norwegian|accessdate=12 March 2010}}</ref> He graduated from the [[University of Oslo]] with a [[cand.mag.]] degree in 1981, took the [[cand.philol.]] degree in 1985 and took the [[dr.philos.]] degree in 1998. In 1997 he was appointed at the [[BI Norwegian Business School]] as professor of economic history, having been an [[associate professor]] since 1991. He has also been a guest scholar at the [[University of Reading]], the [[University of Toulouse]], the [[École supérieure des sciences économiques et commerciales]], the [[Nanyang Technological University]] and the [[ISM University of Management and Economics]].
From 2002 to 2004 he chaired the [[Norwegian Historical Association]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hifo.b.uib.no/om-hifo/historikk/|title=Historikk|publisher=[[Norwegian Historical Association]]|language=Norwegian|accessdate=28 April 2011}}</ref>
Books include the histories of the companies [[Nycomed]], NKS Fjernundervisning, Christiania Glassmagasin as well as BI Norwegian Business School.<ref name=50ar/> He has published 29 articles in international [[academic journal]]s.
